// EntityRef — a typed cross-reference between entities.
//
// Replaces the bare `String` cross-references used throughout 1.0
// (TODO.refactor/1.0-design). Single identity: exactly one of `urn`,
// `identifier`, or `local_ref` should be set. The Ruby class's
// `#valid?` and `#resolved_identity` enforce / pick whichever is set.
//
// Optional metadata:
//   kind — discriminator for the reference's purpose within its profile
//          (e.g. "resulting", "brought_by", "votes_on").
//   role — semantic role of the reference (e.g. "outcome", "source").
//   note — free-form annotation.
//
// The pilot field is `Motion.resultingDecisionRef` (parallel to the
// existing `resultingDecision: String`). 1.0 will remove the String
// form once all consumers have migrated.
class EntityRef {
  urn: String
  identifier: StructuredIdentifier
  localRef: String

  kind: String
  role: String
  note: String
}
